expectvalue /Class
doit
PythonInstance comment:
'Common base class for Python user classes generated by compileClassDef.

Python instances support arbitrary dynamic attributes: any assignment
``obj.x = y`` adds (or replaces) attribute ``x``.  Smalltalk classes
have fixed instVar layouts, so Python attributes that are not
discovered by the __init__ scan are stored in the per-instance
``___dict___`` IdentityKeyValueDictionary.

The DNU handler intercepts unknown env-1 messages and routes them:
  ``obj name:`` (1-keyword, 1 arg)   → setter:  ___dict___ at: #name put: arg.
  ``obj name``  (unary, 0 args)       → getter:  ___dict___ at: #name (or super).

Fixed instVar slots discovered at compile time still get explicit
getter/setter methods (faster path); DNU is the fallback for the rest.'
%

expectvalue /Class
doit
PythonInstance category: 'Modules'
%

! ------------------- Remove existing behavior
removeallmethods PythonInstance
